      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a debate, but like, if you look at the actual text of the amendment, doesn't the originalist view seem a lot more logically consistent with the way the rest of the constitution is read? it feels like the \"living constitution\" crowd is just making up rules as they go to fit modern politics.",
