      "content": "You are pointing to a core tenet of originalist thought, which prioritizes the text's fixed meaning over evolving societal norms. From this perspective, applying the text consistently strengthens the perceived logical coherence of the entire constitutional framework. Conversely, critics of strict originalism argue that failing to account for changing understandings of rights can lead to rigidity that doesn't serve contemporary justice. This tension between textual fidelity and evolving societal needs forms the heart of the constitutional debate.",
      "source": "target",
