      "content": "That fear—that constitutional interpretation slides into mere political policy—is the central concern of originalists. They worry that subjective judicial philosophy can undermine the very rule of law the Constitution establishes. The \"living constitution\" proponents counter that rigidly clinging to 18th-century understandings renders the document incapable of governing a modern, diverse society. Finding a balance between enduring text and contemporary application remains the most profound interpretive challenge in constitutional law.",
